.TH OVCP 8 "July 2026" "ovcp" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
ovcp \- OpenVPN Control Plane: web UI, native PKI, and lifecycle management for an OpenVPN server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ovcp
[\fB\-data\fR \fIDIR\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ovcp
is a single static binary that manages one OpenVPN server: a built\-in
certificate authority (no easy\-rsa), client profile export, server
configuration, and a web admin UI. It talks to the running
.BR openvpn (8)
process over its management \fIunix socket\fR (status and disconnects) and
owns everything else through files in its data directory.
.B ovcp
runs as root, is the sole owner of the PKI and configuration, and starts
openvpn itself as a reaped foreground child \(en the same on the host, under
systemd, and inside the container.
.PP
The CA private key is stored encrypted (argon2id + AES\-256\-GCM). Every
signing operation (issue, revoke) requires the CA passphrase, which is
used in memory and never persisted: compromise of the host alone does not
compromise the CA.
.SH QUICK START
.nf
.RS
# 1. one\-shot setup: CA, server cert, tls\-crypt key, config, admin user
ovcp init \-server\-cn vpn.example.com

# 2. run (admin UI on https://127.0.0.1:8443)
ovcp serve

# 3. hand out a client profile
ovcp export \-cn alice \-remote vpn.example.com > alice.ovpn
.RE
.fi
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init \fB\-server\-cn\fR \fIHOST\fR [\fB\-ca\-cn\fR \fINAME\fR] [\fB\-ca\-years\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-server\-days\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-admin\fR \fINAME\fR] [\fB\-sock\fR \fIPATH\fR]
One\-shot initialization. Creates the CA (prompting twice for a new
passphrase), issues the server certificate for \fIHOST\fR, generates the
tls\-crypt key, writes \fIserver.conf\fR, and creates the initial admin
user. Idempotent: existing artifacts are kept. Pass \fB\-admin\fR "" to
skip user creation.
.TP
.B serve [\fB\-listen\fR \fIADDR\fR] [\fB\-sock\fR \fIPATH\fR]
Run the HTTPS admin UI and REST API (default \fI127.0.0.1:8443\fR, self\-signed
certificate generated on first run). Starts the
.B openvpn
worker from \fIserver.conf\fR as a foreground child (reaped on exit \(en no
zombies) with its log in \fIopenvpn.log\fR, and stops it on clean shutdown.
Exposes a root\-only control socket so a separate
.B ovcp vpn
invocation can drive the worker. Refuses to start with an
actionable error if
.B ovcp init
has not been run.
.TP
.B issue \fB\-cn\fR \fINAME\fR [\fB\-kind\fR client|server] [\fB\-days\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-out\fR \fIPREFIX\fR] [\fB\-key\-pass\fR \fIPW\fR]
Issue a certificate. Client private keys are printed (or written with
\fB\-out\fR) exactly once and never stored; if lost, revoke and reissue.
Certificates (public) are kept and can be re\-downloaded anytime with
\fBlist\fR / the web UI. With \fB\-key\-pass\fR the private key is
AES\-256 encrypted; OpenVPN prompts for the password on connect.
.TP
.B export \fB\-cn\fR \fINAME\fR \fB\-remote\fR \fIHOST\fR [\fB\-port\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-proto\fR udp|tcp] [\fB\-server\-cn\fR \fICN\fR]
Issue a fresh client certificate and print a complete inline
\fI.ovpn\fR profile (CA, cert, key, tls\-crypt) on stdout. Accepts
\fB\-key\-pass\fR to password\-protect the embedded key.
.TP
.B revoke \fB\-serial\fR \fIHEX\fR
Revoke a certificate and regenerate the CRL. OpenVPN rejects the client
on its next handshake (\fBcrl\-verify\fR is always configured).
.TP
.B list
List issued certificates with status (valid, REVOKED, expired).
.TP
.B status [\fB\-sock\fR \fIPATH\fR]
Show currently connected VPN clients via the management socket.
.TP
.B kill \fB\-cn\fR \fINAME\fR [\fB\-sock\fR \fIPATH\fR]
Disconnect a client immediately.
.TP
.B genconfig [\fB\-out\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB\-proto\fR udp|tcp] [\fB\-port\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB\-subnet\fR \fICIDR\fR] [\fB\-dns\fR \fIIPs\fR]
Render \fIserver.conf\fR from options (stdout by default). Normally not
needed:
.B init
and
.B serve
maintain the file.
.TP
.B vpn start|stop|restart|reconnect
Manage the openvpn worker owned by a running
.B serve
(over the control socket, see \fBOVCP_CTRL_SOCK\fR).
.B start
launches it (idempotent),
.B stop
sends SIGTERM,
.B restart
is a full stop + fresh start \(en required for any configuration, key, or
CRL change \(en and
.B reconnect
sends SIGUSR1 for a soft session reset (runtime recovery, no process
replacement). SIGHUP / in\-place reload is intentionally not supported: a
fresh restart re\-reads every root\-owned file, which SIGHUP cannot.
.TP
.B user add|list|disable|enable|passwd|totp
Manage web UI users. Roles: \fBadmin\fR (everything), \fBoperator\fR
(certificates, disconnects), \fBreadonly\fR.
.B user totp
prints an otpauth:// enrollment URL.
.TP
.B audit
Print the last 50 audit entries (logins, issues, revocations, kills,
config changes).
.TP
.B version
Print the version.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-data \fIDIR\fR
Data directory (default \fI/var/lib/ovcp\fR, or \fB$OVCP_DATA\fR).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OVCP_DATA
Data directory.
.TP
.B OVCP_LISTEN
Admin UI listen address(es), comma\-separated. Each gets the full
HTTPS/auth stack. VPN\-side addresses (e.g. 10.8.0.1:8443, reachable by
connected clients) may be bound before the tun interface exists
(IP_FREEBIND).
.TP
.B OVCP_MGMT_SOCK
OpenVPN management socket path (default \fI/run/ovcp/mgmt.sock\fR).
.TP
.B OVCP_CTRL_SOCK
ovcp control socket for \fBvpn\fR subcommands (default
\fI/run/ovcp/control.sock\fR); the CLI talks to a running \fBserve\fR here.
.TP
.B OVCP_SERVER_CN
Default client \fBremote\fR for \fBexport\fR and CN for the admin UI
certificate (falls back to the VPN server certificate's CN).
.TP
.B OVCP_CA_PASSPHRASE, OVCP_USER_PASSWORD
Non\-interactive passphrase/password for automation, tests, and container
init (the image defaults both to \fIchangeme\fR). Avoid on
shared systems: environment variables can leak.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/pki/ca.crt, ca.key.enc
CA certificate and encrypted private key.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/pki/server.crt, server.key
Server keypair used by openvpn.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/pki/crl.pem
Certificate revocation list (referenced by \fBcrl\-verify\fR).
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/pki/tls\-crypt.key
OpenVPN static key for tls\-crypt (control channel encryption).
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/server.conf
Generated openvpn configuration. Managed by ovcp; do not edit.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/ovcp.db
SQLite database: users, sessions, certificate metadata, audit log.
Private keys are never stored in the database.
.TP
.I /var/lib/ovcp/admin\-tls/
Self\-signed certificate for the admin UI.
.TP
.I /run/ovcp/mgmt.sock, /run/ovcp/control.sock
OpenVPN management socket (unix only, never TCP) and ovcp's root\-only
(0600) control socket for \fBvpn\fR lifecycle ops.
.SH EXAMPLES
Issue and download a profile for a phone, valid two years:
.nf
.RS
ovcp export \-cn dana\-phone \-remote vpn.example.com > dana\-phone.ovpn
.RE
.fi
Revoke it later:
.nf
.RS
ovcp list
ovcp revoke \-serial 682b2da83f4d...
.RE
.fi
Run under systemd (after installing the package):
.nf
.RS
ovcp init \-server\-cn vpn.example.com
systemctl enable \-\-now ovcp
.RE
.fi
.SH PRIVILEGES
.B ovcp
runs as root and is the sole owner of the PKI and configuration
(\fI0600 root:root\fR), so those files are secure by default \(en there is
no privilege drop and no per\-mode juggling. It starts openvpn, which needs
root or CAP_NET_ADMIN at startup and then drops to \fInobody\fR on its own.
In containers, run with \-\-cap\-add NET_ADMIN; the runtime dir
\fI/run/ovcp\fR (0750) holds the management and control sockets. openvpn
runs as a foreground child of ovcp and cannot outlive it (Pdeathsig).
A future unprivileged IPC worker will be a separate process, not a drop
inside ovcp.
.SH SELINUX
On SELinux systems the confined
.BR openvpn (8)
domain cannot read a non\-standard data directory. Run
\fIdeploy/selinux.sh\fR once (labels the data dir \fIopenvpn_etc_t\fR and
the logs \fIopenvpn_var_log_t\fR; honors \fB$OVCP_DATA\fR). ovcp itself
runs unconfined and needs no policy.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR openvpn (8),
.BR systemctl (1)
